		{"id":"7656b5cb73cb303d","type":"text","text":"chungus\npibble x bape\ni am pibble wash my bellay\nchipi chipi chapa\nskeleton running eyes\nRAAAUUGH skeleton banging shield\nskeletons judging berserk\nagartha yakub\nhm hm hm dog\nhenry ayveries\nson im crine\nfahhhh","x":8360,"y":-460,"width":380,"height":480},
		{"id":"b582f3e6b534e552","type":"text","text":"what's the best way of making creatures aware of how near they are to walls?\n\n(probably raycasting)\n\nonce they have data representing their vicinity to walls, how do i influence the creature's movement to prefer spots closer to walls?\n\nhow do i define \"closer to walls\"?\n\n```gdscript\nextends Node\nclass_name MovementComponent\n\n@export var max_speed: float = 100.0\n@export var acceleration: float = 500.0\n@export var friction: float = 800.0 # how fast it stopps\n@export var rotation_speed: float = 10.0 # for smooth turning\n\n\nvar velocity: Vector2 = Vector2.ZERO\nvar desired_direction: Vector2 = Vector2.ZERO\n\nsignal started_moving(direction: Vector2)\nsignal stopped_moving()\nsignal changed_direction(old_direction: Vector2, new_direction: Vector2)\n\n\nvar moving: bool = false\n\nfunc set_desired_direction(dir: Vector2) -> void:\n\tif dir.length() > 0:\n\t\tdesired_direction = dir.normalized()\n\telse:\n\t\tdesired_direction = Vector2.ZERO\n\t\nfunc physics_update(delta: float, body: CharacterBody2D) -> void:\n\tmovement_function(delta, body)\n\t\t\n\tdetect_active_movement()\n\t\n\tbody.move_and_slide()\n\t\nfunc movement_function(delta: float, body: CharacterBody2D) -> void:\n\tif desired_direction.length() > 0:\n\t\tvar target_velocity = desired_direction * max_speed\n\t\tvelocity = velocity.move_toward(target_velocity, acceleration * delta)\n\telse:\n\t\tvelocity = velocity.move_toward(Vector2.ZERO, friction * delta)\n\tbody.velocity = velocity\n\t\t\nfunc detect_active_movement() -> void:\n\tif abs(velocity.x) < 0.05 or abs(velocity.y) < 0.05:\n\t\tif moving:\n\t\t\tstopped_moving.emit()\n\t\tmoving = false\n\telse:\n\t\tif not moving:\n\t\t\tstarted_moving.emit(velocity.normalized())\n\t\tmoving = true \n\t\t\n\t\n\n```\n\nthis is the default movement component, but it is easy to overload the movement function to compute velocity in different ways.\n\nit might also be necessary to do post processing on pathfinding!\n\n```gdscript\nextends State\nclass_name PathfindWanderState\n\n@export var movement: MovementComponent\n@export var wall_avoidance: WallAvoidance\n@export var target_seeker: TargetSeeker\n@export var navigation_agent: NavigationAgent2D\n\n@export var animator: SpriteAnimator\n@export var facing: FacingComponent\n\n@export_group(\"States\")\n@export var chase_state: State\n@export var idle_state: State\n@export_group(\"Variables\")\n\n@export var timer_length: float = 5.0\nvar wander_timer: float = 0.0\nvar wander_direction: Vector2 = Vector2.ZERO\n@export var wander_radius: float = 250.0\n\n\nsignal picked_new_path(target_position: Vector2)\nsignal found_target(target: Node2D)\nsignal interrupted()\n\nfunc enter() -> void:\n\t_pick_new_pathfinding_location(owner.position)\n\tif target_seeker:\n\t\ttarget_seeker.target_found.connect(_on_target_found)\n\t\t\n\tif navigation_agent:\n\t\tnavigation_agent.navigation_finished.connect(_on_navigation_finished)\n\t\t\n\tinterrupted.connect(_decide_if_idle)\n\t\n\tfound_target.connect(_on_target_found)\n\t\n\tif animator:\n\t\tanimator.load_animation(\"walk\")\n\t\t\nfunc update(delta: float) -> void:\n\tvar old_wander_direction: Vector2 = wander_direction\n\twander_timer -= delta\n\tif wander_timer <= 0:\n\t\tinterrupted.emit()\n\t\t_pick_new_pathfinding_location(owner.position)\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\nfunc physics_update(delta: float) -> void:\n\tvar next_path_position: Vector2 = navigation_agent.get_next_path_position()\n\twander_direction = (next_path_position - owner.global_position).normalized()\n\tvar steering = wander_direction\n\t\n\t\n\tif wall_avoidance:\n\t\tvar avoidance = wall_avoidance.get_avoidance_vector(owner.global_position)\n\t\tsteering += avoidance\n\t\t\n\tif target_seeker:\n\t\tvar target = target_seeker.find_nearest_target(\n\t\t\towner.global_position,\n\t\t\tmovement.velocity.normalized()\n\t\t)\n\t\t\n\t\tif target:\n\t\t\tfound_target.emit(target)\n\t\t\n\tmovement.set_desired_direction(steering)\n\t\n\tmovement.physics_update(delta, owner)\n\t\n\tif animator:\n\t\tanimator.update_animation(delta, movement.velocity.length() * 0.2)\n\t\t\n\tif facing:\n\t\tfacing.change_direction(steering)\n\nfunc exit() -> void:\n\tif target_seeker:\n\t\ttarget_seeker.target_found.disconnect(_on_target_found)\n\t\t\n\tif navigation_agent:\n\t\tnavigation_agent.navigation_finished.disconnect(_on_navigation_finished)\n\t\t\n\tinterrupted.disconnect(_decide_if_idle)\n\t\n\tfound_target.disconnect(_on_target_found)\n\t\t\nfunc _pick_new_pathfinding_location(origin: Vector2) -> void:\n\tvar angle: float = randf() * TAU\n\tvar distance = randf() * wander_radius\n\tvar target_position: Vector2 = origin + Vector2(cos(angle), sin(angle)) * distance\n\tnavigation_agent.set_target_position(target_position)\n\twander_timer = timer_length\n\tpicked_new_path.emit(target_position)\n\t\nfunc _on_navigation_finished() -> void:\n\tinterrupted.emit()\n\t_pick_new_pathfinding_location(owner.position)\n\nfunc _on_target_found(target: Node2D) -> void:\n\tif chase_state:\n\t\tstate_machine.switch(chase_state)\n\n\nfunc _decide_if_idle() -> void:\n\tvar chance: float = 0.3\n\tif randf() < 0.3:\n\t\tstate_machine.switch(idle_state)\n\n```\n\nthis is my basic pathfinding and wandering script. it could be necessary to alter the `_pick_new_pathfinding_location()` function to either avoid or pick a point near walls. there could be a distance calculation and if the distance is not satisfactory, another point would be generated and chosen.\n\nwalls are on collision layer 1, so i'd have to make sure that the raycasts (or however way the walls are detected) are on collision mask 1.","x":10200,"y":-1980,"width":780,"height":3900},
		{"id":"f536f835e5ec71d8","type":"text","text":"**salmon**\n\nflops around aimlessly\n> perhaps figure out some magic involving shadows; the fish's sprite should hop and bounce when it moves.\n\nshoots pellets at nearby creatures\n> this is easy, just have to make a pellet object and add a hurtbox to it. it shouldn't collide with terrain. let's just make this a characterbody2d.\n> targets can be any creature.\n\nlikes being in water\n> this can come later, involves giving custom properties to tiles. maybe consider buying tilesetter for texturing?\n> maybe the salmon can behave differently in the water","x":4080,"y":-1840,"width":540,"height":380},
		{"id":"94bbe267d1f7db6a","type":"text","text":"**rud**\n\nhops strategically\n> not sure what this means\n> im sure the rud wants to stay within a certain radius of a water tile, but other than that i think the rud will also just hop around in random directions.\n> i don't think the rud can jump over walls.\n\neats salmon\n> perhaps create a hunger component and then use that; when under a threshold the rud hunts.\n> when hunting, another threshold will have to be surpassed to calm the rud down.\n> or maybe when there's a nearby salmon, there's a percent chance each second that the rud decides to hunt it. that's probably a better idea. this could be a component which emits a signal\n\ncauses shockwaves when it hops\n> a simple hurtbox and particle. use a signal to connect this to when the frog \"lands\" after hopping.","x":4080,"y":-1440,"width":540,"height":470},
		{"id":"4a230eed43f25a89","type":"text","text":"**bitwit**\n\nis knocked around easily\n> i think i might need to make a knockback component for this. something that basically disables any sort of movement and pretty much changes the creature into a rigidbody that slides around.\n> any time the bitwit is collided into at a threshold speed, this state should be switched into for a period of time\n\nfollows creatures around\n> wanders around except for when it decides to pick a target creature to follow around closely. this is probably on interval or a random chance every second.\n> bitwits are more likely to choose targets that have more bitwits already following.\n> this would just be a call to the targetseeker and then a state switch to get the target's position and pathfind towards that.\n\nbitwits are small\n> they are a lot smaller than the average size creature (16px), i'm thinking probably 8px small","x":4640,"y":-1840,"width":540,"height":470},
		{"id":"167b9cdbef28029d","type":"text","text":"**floroid**\n\ncompanion fruit\n> for now, we can have this just be eaten instantly, there will need to be animations and sound later\n> lateron also we can add in stuff like stages and graphics and stuff\n\ndigs underground\n> basically this would just be hiding the sprite or changing it to something different and also disabling its hitbox and collision box.\n> maybe increase the movement speed or have it use a differnet movement function while underground\n> particles and fun stuff later\n\ncomes up occasionally to drop a fruit\n> this can just be on a timer, like a range or something\n> TODO: add a component for a timer with a range\n\ndamages walls it digs under\n> this is more tricky and involves mapping a pixel coordinate position to a tile unit position.\n> i've made systems before that give tiles properties so all i would have to do is store these properties in a data structure using the tile unit position as a key.\n> translate the coordinate position into the tile position and use that as the key to get the cell at that coordinate, then update its statistics.\n> any changes to the statistics will be reflected visually by the tilemaplayer. no changes are to be made to the collision boxes or navigation meshes of any tiles (it won't be necessary)\n\n","x":3600,"y":-1840,"width":460,"height":720},
		{"id":"4a04a95aba69295d","type":"file","file":"assets/a8a7dcec34fd2b1cbe978486706f5a9a.gif","x":8600,"y":-3507,"width":844,"height":407},
		{"id":"0a113eed4a7cc760","type":"text","text":"**pellet**\n\na projectile works differently to a character.\nprojectiles have a hitbox and a hurtbox.\nsome projectiles will take damage or die when their hurtbox is contacted.\n\nit's a bit fucked up because collision and damage is handled on the side of the victim. the victim takes damage when their hitbox comes in contact with a hurtbox.\n\nso how do i add exceptions so that the originator of a pellet doesn't take damage?\n\na FriendComponent?\n\nso hurtbox -> hitbox -> healthcomponent (take_damage)\n\nokay so i could just add a FriendComponent to the salmon, then when a pellet needs to be spawned, then add it to a list in the friendcomponent. if the friend's hurtbox touches the salmon's hitbox, then nothing should happen since it's in the list.\n\nthere should be functions to add and remove friends. if a friend needs to be retrieved, then all invalid instances should be removed from the list first.","x":3200,"y":-1040,"width":640,"height":620},
		{"id":"3766a7824e732e7e","type":"text","text":"creature state loops\n\n**cow**\npathfindwander --(hunger)--> pathfindwanderandseek --(found)--> chasetarget --(vicinity)--> eat --(finished)--> pathfindwander\n\n**imp**\npathfindwander --(vicinity)--> standstillandattack --(not in vicinity)--> pathfindwander\n\n**plopp**\npathfindwander --(interval)--> plop --(finished)--> pathfindwander\n\n**stone**\npathfindwanderpreferwalls\n\n**salmon**\npathfindwanderpreferwater --(interval)--> pathfindwanderandseek --(found)--> standstillandattack --(done)--> pathfindwanderpreferwater\n\n**rud**\npathfindwanderpreferwater --(hunger)--> pathfindwanderandseek --(found)--> chasetarget --(vicinity)--> eat --(finished)--> pathfindwanderpreferwater\n\n**bitwit**\npathfindwander --(interval)--> pathfindwanderandseek --(vicinity)--> idle","x":1880,"y":-1020,"width":1120,"height":660},
		{"id":"4c913f3fdbad3401","type":"file","file":"assets/856fc6f45e9767d17770232b3d3c51f2.jpg","x":5360,"y":-4373,"width":333,"height":400},
		{"id":"30a91b02e321331f","type":"file","file":"assets/59f40038822864e4daac697a89b2e5a3.jpg","x":4960,"y":-4173,"width":400,"height":328},
